## Store/Cart Frontend Contracts

- `storeCartItemsAtom` persists in local storage as `store.cart`.
- Product/category/catalog atoms persist as `store.products` and `store.categories`.
- Store catalog filters include category, unified product/category/seller search,
  price, rating, sort, and an authenticated `You` owner toggle.
  Price bounds should tolerate inverted min/max input by treating the lower value
  as the minimum.
- Store catalog and order filters use the reusable `FilterBar`; dense order filters
  render through the `TableView` toolbar and cover search, order/payment status,
  and date/total sorting without replacing the live `ordersAtom` source.
- Store chrome may show live wallet balance and pending-order badges fetched from
  `/store/wallet` and `/store/orders`; wallet badges compact thousands as `$1.2k`
  or `$12k`, pending counts include open vendor line status, and loaded user
  orders should be subscribed to for live badge updates.
- Cart page supports authenticated carts and guest checkout from local cart items.
- Empty cart state uses the compact storefront empty-state treatment with
  "No products added" copy, not a large CTA card.
- Checkout payload includes `items`, `payment_method_id`, `currency`, guest contact,
  delivery fields, `billing_info`, and `referral_code`.
- Saved checkout details live in local storage key `checkoutSaved`; do not save
  `deliveryTime`.
- Authenticated users may load wallet cards from `/store/wallet/cards` and pay with
  `card_{id}` or `wallet`.
- Successful checkout clears local cart and shows the submitted order view.
- Order status views surface per-vendor activity in the right summary column with
  compact vendor totals, status, and accept/reject controls for the current
  vendor's own line items.
- Rich inline users in global messages should render all available roles using
  the role catalog colors when only role names are embedded in the message user.
  Inline user cards and profile overlays must share in-flight user/role catalog
  requests so dense chat/message views do not stampede `/users/roles`.
- System inbox messages containing JSON payloads, especially order cards, render
  as compact inline interactive cards that route to the canonical destination
  such as `/store/orders/{id}` and do not echo raw JSON as a caption.
- Global chat join/leave rows use compact colored arrow icons: green right arrow
  for join and red left arrow for leave.
- Presence DEFCON tab includes a compact reset control that clears runtime
  DEFCON state and refreshes telemetry for admins.

## CSS Token Contract

All UI colors, shadows, radii, and fonts must route through global tokens in
`src/index.css`.

| Token family | Use |
| --- | --- |
| `--primary-*`, `--skaia-green-primary` | brand/actions |
| `--bg-*`, `--text-*`, `--border-color` | layout and text |
| `--error-*`, `--success-*`, `--warning-*`, `--info-*` | semantic state |
| `--shadow`, `--shadow-hover`, `--focus-ring` | elevation/focus |
| `--card-*`, `--section-*`, `--panel-*` | repeated containers |
| `--module-*` | activity/module badges |
| `--font-mono` | all monospace text |

## CSS Rules

- Component CSS must not hardcode hex/rgb/rgba colors; use tokens and
  `color-mix(in srgb, var(--token) X%, transparent)` for alpha.
- Do not use `var()` fallbacks.
- Dark mode is `html[data-theme="dark"]`; do not use
  `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)`.
- Use shared shadows; add a token before introducing a new shadow.
- Card-like containers use `.card`; section containers use `.section`.
- Semantic and form-like containers use `.compact-form-card` for the shared transparent
  flat-glass surface while retaining domain layout classes. Form groups keep comfortable
  separation, labels explain their controls, major actions use `Button`, and icon-only
  actions use the `action-btn`/typed button variants.
- Icon-only buttons use `.thread-action-btn` plus size/variant modifiers.
- `!important` is allowed only for third-party overrides, page-builder inline
  alignment overrides, intentional resets, or mobile grid collapse.
- Component CSS should primarily own layout, positioning, overflow, and animation.

## UI Layout Contracts

- List/feed pages use dense, scannable layouts: toolbar first, responsive grid/list
  below, max width around 1400px unless an editor needs more.
- Fixed-format elements need stable dimensions to prevent hover/content layout shift.
- Page-builder editor panes collapse below tablet widths.
- Guest sandbox mode reveals management controls in the frontend only; backend auth
  remains the authority.
- Do not add marketing landing pages when building app functionality.

