## Invariants

- High-fanout rich-user mounts use `apiRequestLazy`. It deduplicates unresolved
  keys, collects unique IDs in a short window, caps batches, resolves callers
  individually, and deletes entries on settlement; it must not become a
  resolved-value cache.
- Rich-user results publish to every mounted card/overlay for that user. Chat or
  JWT names are fallbacks only; failures retry once and broken avatar URLs may
  trigger one guarded refresh per mounted consumer.

- Do not create a second global WebSocket connection.
- Do not poll for data that has a WS projection.
- Custom-page views subscribe to `page:{id}`. The singleton subscription set is
  replayed after reconnect and `usePageData` then performs an authoritative REST
  refetch so missed section/theme revisions cannot remain hidden.
- Do not duplicate token definitions in component CSS.
- Do not persist sensitive card CVV-like data in frontend local storage.
- Backend permissions are authoritative; frontend permission checks are UX only.

## Verify

- CSS drift: `rg "#[0-9a-fA-F]{3,8}|rgba\\(|rgb\\(|var\\([^)]*," frontend/src --glob '*.css'`
- WS usage: `rg "useWebSocketSync|subscribe\\(|unsubscribe\\(" frontend/src -n`
- Store/cart: `frontend/src/pages/cart/index.tsx`, `frontend/src/atoms/store.ts`
- Tests/build when relevant: run frontend package scripts from `frontend/`.

